{{refimprove|date=August 2018}}
{{Infobox video game | title = Bad Street Brawler | image = Bad Street Brawler cover.png | caption = NES version package | developer = [[Beam Software|Beam Software Pty., Ltd.]] | publisher = [[Mindscape Group|Mindscape Inc.]] | composer = Gavan Anderson and Tania Smith (NES version) | released = 1987 | genre = [[Beat 'em up]] | modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]] | platforms = [[Commodore 64]], [[MS-DOS]], [[Nintendo Entertainment System|NES]] }}
'''''Bad Street Brawler''''' is a {{vgy|1987}} [[video game]] by [[Beam Software|Beam Software Pty., Ltd.]] It was distributed worldwide by [[Mindscape Group|Mindscape Inc.]] and [[Mattel]]. It was released for the [[Commodore 64]], [[MS-DOS]], and the [[Nintendo Entertainment System|NES]]. The NES version was one of only two NES games specifically designed for use with [[Mattel]]'s [[Power Glove]].
==Gameplay== [[Image:BadStreetBrawlerSSTrip.png|left|thumb|256px|In-game screenshot]]
The player plays the character Duke Davis, who goes from stage to stage beating up [[gangsters]] that get in his way, dressed in a yellow [[Tank top (shirt)|tank top]], [[sunglasses]], and yellow pants. He is described as a former [[punk rock]]er and the "world's coolest" [[martial artist]].
Before the start of the next stage, quotes are introduced to entertain the player (such as "Never trouble trouble until trouble troubles you"). The player fights a variety of enemies, such as [[gorilla]]s and circus [[Dwarfism|dwarves]] who throw [[hammer throw|hammers]] at the player (resembling old ladies in the DOS port who throw purses at the player). There are 15 stages in this game Moves include the "bull ram" attack and "trip" move.
==Reception== ''[[Electronic Gaming Monthly]]''{{'}}s [[Seanbaby]] placed it as number 16 in his "20 worst games of all time" feature.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seanbaby.com:80/nes/egm16.htm|title=Seanbaby's EGM's Crapstravaganza - #16: Bad Street Brawler (NES)|website=Seanbaby.com|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060707231735/http://www.seanbaby.com/nes/egm16.htm|archivedate=2006-07-07|deadurl=yes|access-date=2007-01-29|df=}}</ref>
